                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2603.04254/2603.04254v1/fig/main.png",
                "caption": "Figure 2:Overall framework of our EmbodiedSplat.We endow feed-forward 3DGS with semantic understanding capabilities by binding the two types of CLIP features: 1)2D Semantic Featuresare attached to each Gaussian viaSparse Coefficient FieldwithCLIP Global Codebook, effectively reducing memory consumption while preserving semantic generalizability of CLIP. 2)3D Geometric-aware Featuresare produced by aggregating the feature point cloud of 3DGS through 3D U-Net[10]and temporal-aware memory adapter[75]. These two types of features enable mutual compensation between semantic and 3D geometry, which results in superior understanding capabilities compared to the existing baselines.",
